text: Rosa Delia Cota Montaño (born 23 April 1951) is a Mexican politician from the Labor Party. From 2000 to 2003 she served as Deputy of the LVIII Legislature of the Mexican Congress representing Baja California Sur. ==References== Category:1951 births Category:Living people Category:Politicians from Baja California Sur Category:Women members of the Chamber of Deputies (Mexico) Category:Members of the Chamber of Deputies (Mexico) Category:Labor Party (Mexico) politicians Category:21st-century Mexican politicians Category:21st- century Mexican women politicians Category:People from Los Cabos Municipality
title: Rosa Delia Cota Montaño
